com.cyc.kb

Interface Variable

  • All Superinterfaces:
    KbObject
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    VariableWrapper

    public interface Variable
extends KbObject
    The interface for CycL variables. Variables are used in quantified Sentences and in Queries.

    • Method Detail

      • get

        static Variable get(String varStr)
             throws KbTypeException
        Creates an instance of #$CycLVariable represented by varStr in the underlying KB. This static method wraps a call to VariableService.get(java.lang.String); see that method's documentation for more details.
        Specified by:
        get in interface KbObject
        Parameters:
        varStr - the string representing an #$CycLVariable in the KB
        Returns:
        the Variable representing an #$CycLVariable in the KB
        Throws:
        KbTypeException - if the term represented by varStr is not an instance of #$CycLVariable and cannot be made into one. Symbols are created on demand and are not expected to throw any exception
        See Also:
        KbService.getKbObject(java.lang.String)
